  User C (Owner) Adds User B as a Collaborator
o    GitHub → Repository Settings → Collaborators → Add User B → Submit



2.    User B Forks the Repository & Clones It Locally

git clone https://github.com/durainbrindha/URK24CS1257.git
cd URK24CS1257

3.    User B Links to the Upstream Repository for Updates
git remote add upstream https://github.com/durainbrindha/URK24CS1257.git

4.    User B Pulls Latest Changes from the Owner
git pull upstream main

Note pull in user B in github

5.    User B Creates a New Branch for Work
git checkout -b urknew

create a file or update ib drive

6.    User B Makes Changes & Commits
git add .
git commit -m "Added urknewfile"

7.    User B Pushes Changes to Their Fork
git push origin urknew

8.    User B Submits a Pull Request on GitHub
o    Go to the forked repository → Click Compare & Pull Request → Submit

9.    User C Reviews & Merges the Pull Request

10.    User B Syncs with the Owner's Repository for Future Updates
    git checkout main
